description.plain: Yael Naim is an Israeli-French singer-songwriter and instrumentalist. She is most known for the song “New Soul” which was sampled by many hip hop artists. New Soul was also featured in an Apple Macbook TV commercial.

description.plain: “New Soul” is a song by the French-Israeli indie folk singer Yael Naïm, from her self-titled album. The song gained popularity in the United States following its use by Apple in an advertisement for their MacBook Air laptop.  It remains Naïm’s biggest hit single in the U.S. to date, and her only one to reach the Top 10 of the Billboard Hot 100.

description.plain:
Yael Naim was born in Paris and grew up in Israel. She regularly sings in english and hebrew.

In 2015, year the album Older was released she announced the birth of her first child, a daughter. She also lost her grandmother.

Another song in the album Older is called “Make a Child”, while another one called “Ima” contains lyrics in hebrew.

Source of this bio.

This mix of events and facts about her life give credence to the various readings that can be had of this particular song.

The clip of this song was co-directed by Stromae.
